# CODEOWNERS — automatic PR reviewer assignment
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Format : <pattern>  <owner> [<owner> ...]
# Rules are evaluated top-to-bottom; the LAST matching rule wins.
# Docs   : https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Default: catch-all (every file not matched below) ────────────────────────
*                               @LIN4CRE

# ── Repository meta & documentation ──────────────────────────────────────────
/*.md                           @LIN4CRE
/LICENSE                        @LIN4CRE
/VERSION                        @LIN4CRE
/requirements.txt               @LIN4CRE
/.gitignore                     @LIN4CRE

# ── Source code ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Upgrade to @LIN4CRE/backend once that team is created in the org
/src/                           @LIN4CRE

# ── Tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Upgrade to @LIN4CRE/qa once that team is created in the org
/tests/                         @LIN4CRE

# ── Scripts (quality, tooling) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
/scripts/                       @LIN4CRE

# ── CI/CD & repository configuration (highest sensitivity) ───────────────────
# Upgrade to @LIN4CRE/devops once that team is created in the org
/.github/                       @LIN4CRE
/.github/workflows/             @LIN4CRE
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @LIN4CRE
